cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the impact of base station idle mode capability on network performance in small cell networks, which is a networking topic. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the area spectral efficiency (ASE) performance, which is a key metric in information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of a system (small cell network) with idle mode capability, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may have implications for multimedia applications in small cell networks, as the coverage probability and ASE performance are important for delivering high-quality multimedia content. 
5. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper may be relevant to multi-agent systems, as small cell networks can be viewed as a collection of agents (base stations) that interact with each other and with users.
